2:T8d3,[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Place","name":"Harlem","description":"Harlem is one of the world's most culturally significant neighborhoods — the historical center of African American intellectual, artistic, and political life in the 20th century, and a neighborhood un","url":"https://withpush.co/neighborhoods/harlem","geo":{"@type":"GeoCoordinates","latitude":40.8116,"longitude":-73.9465},"address":{"@type":"PostalAddress","addressLocality":"Harlem","addressRegion":"NY","addressCountry":"US"},"containedInPlace":{"@type":"City","name":"New York City"}},{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How does Push work in Harlem?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Push connects local creators with merchants in Harlem, Manhattan. Creators visit participating businesses, scan a QR code to verify their visit, then publish content. Merchants pay only for verified foot traffic — no guessing required."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many campaigns are active in Harlem right now?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Harlem currently has 23 active creator campaigns across 28 merchants, with 104 creators operating in this neighborhood."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the average campaign payout in Harlem?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The average campaign payout in Harlem is $36 per verified visit. Total verified visits in this neighborhood have reached 2,834."}}]},{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"ItemList","name":"Featured Merchants in Harlem","numberOfItems":3,"itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"item":{"@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"Sylvia's Restaurant","address":"328 Malcolm X Blvd, New York, NY 10027","description":"Food & Drink business in Harlem with 1 active Push campaign."}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"item":{"@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"Red Rooster Harlem","address":"310 Lenox Ave, New York, NY 10027","description":"Food & Drink business in Harlem with 2 active Push campaigns."}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"item":{"@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"Hyena Coffee","address":"234 W 125th St, New York, NY 10027","description":"Coffee business in Harlem with 2 active Push campaigns."}}]}]4:T468,Harlem is one of the world's most culturally significant neighborhoods — the historical center of African American intellectual, artistic, and political life in the 20th century, and a neighborhood undergoing careful self-determined renewal in the 21st. 125th Street is the commercial main street: national chains now coexist with legacy barbershops, soul food institutions, and the new wave of Black-owned restaurants and cocktail bars that have made Harlem one of New York's most compelling dining destinations. Push arrived in Harlem at the invitation of its merchant community — local business owners who saw creator marketing as a tool for driving neighborhood-first foot traffic rather than gentrification-accelerating hype. Campaigns here are often explicitly community-focused: supporting businesses run by and for Harlem residents. The creator community in Harlem reflects the neighborhood's demographics more accurately than any other Push market — a genuine representation of the people who live here and care about it. Top categories: Soul Food & Southern, Caribbean, West African, Coffee, Beauty & Barbershop.0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$2"}}],["$","main",null,{"className":"nh-page","children":[["$","section",null,{"className":"nhd-hero","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container nhd-hero-inner","children":[["$","nav",null,{"className":"nhd-breadcrumb","aria-label":"Breadcrumb","children":[["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/","children":"Push"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"nhd-breadcrumb-sep","children":"/"}],["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/neighborhoods","children":"Neighborhoods"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"nhd